Class EditDiscreteNumericalVar

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.va.med.srcalc.web.view.admin.EditBaseVar

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EditVar
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    EditExistingDiscreteNumericalVar

    public class EditDiscreteNumericalVar
extends EditAbstractNumericalVar

    A form backing object for creating a new or editing an existing DiscreteNumericalVariable.

    This code is tightly coupled with newDiscreteNumericalVariable.jsp.

      • getValidator

        public EditDiscreteNumericalVarValidator getValidator()
        Description copied from interface: EditVar

        Returns an appropriate Validator instance for validating this object.

        Implementations do not perform their own validation so that the web code can directly bind user input to these beans without fear of Exceptions. We instead provide a Spring Validator via this method to safely ensure that user input meets the underlying variable class's requirements.

      • getTrimmedCategories

        public final com.google.common.collect.ImmutableList<CategoryBuilder> getTrimmedCategories()

        Like getCategories() but with trailing blank categories trimmed off. A Category is considered blank if its value is blank. (The user still may have inputted an upper bound.)

        This method is useful because we allow the user to delete trailing categories by clearing out the category names.

        Returns:
        an ImmutableList
